Chrysler Canada Ltd, whollyowned by Chrysler Corp, said it sold 16,484 passenger cars inMarch, a 9.7 pct increase over the 15,024 sold in the samemonth of last year.    The company said truck sales rose 32 pct to a March recordof 7,400 units from 5,603 in March of last year.    For the first quarter, car sales totaled 34,578 comparedwith 37,097 a year earlier, while truck sales totaled 15,397compared with 14,069. Reuter&#3;